# JavaScript - functional programming

##functions are a block of code that can be reused

```javascript
function sayHello() {
    console.log("Hello");
}

sayHello(); //calling the function

function sayHelloFN(name) {
    console.log(name);
}

sayHelloFN(name); //undefined
sayHelloFN('sammy'); //sammy

function namestey() {
    return "how to say, Hello in India";
}

namstey(); //prints nothing
let greetings = namestey(); //hold the value of the function
```